    <h2>Lessons Learned</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Always use parameterized queries to prevent SQL injection</li>
      <li>Implement proper rate limiting to prevent automated attacks</li>
      <li>Avoid exposing response time differences that can be exploited</li>
      <li>Use prepared statements instead of string concatenation</li>
    </ul>

    <blockquote>
      "Security is not a product, but a process. Even with multiple layers, a single vulnerability can compromise everything."
    </blockquote>

